title: Direct flights to Macedonian capital Skopje from July
text:
Tuesday, February 28, 2017, 15:27 Direct flights to Macedonian capital Skopje from July Wizz Air announces bi-weekly flights Wizz Air is to begin flying from Malta to Skopje in July. Photo: Shutterstock 
Low-cost carrier Wizz Air is to start flying between Malta and Macedonian capital Skopje twice a week. 
The flights will begin on July 14 and will run all year round, the airline has announced. Presently, passengers wishing to travel between Malta and Skopje must catch a connecting flight from Vienna or Istanbul. 
Wizz Air is the largest airline operating in Macedonia.
